  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The rate of hernia recurrence at one year following repair of a large abdominal hernia with a
      biologic mesh is high, ranging from 30% to 100%, with a reported historic average rate of
      40%. The purpose of this study is to evaluate the rate of hernia recurrence at one year
      following repair with SurgiMend 3.0, an FDA-cleared novel biologic mesh, the hypothesis being
      that such rate will be less than 20% at one year, representing a 50% reduction over the
      historic rate of 40%.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
